abstract: Once acquaintances as members of the wealthy Manhattan elite, Michael Bloomberg and President Trump have become bitter rivals. And a flurry of Bloomberg attack ads is angering the president.
snippet: Once acquaintances as members of the wealthy Manhattan elite, Michael Bloomberg and President Trump have become bitter rivals. And a flurry of Bloomberg attack ads is angering the president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A few days after Election Day in 2016, Donald J. Trump received a call on his cellphone from Michael R. Bloomberg, an old acquaintance he had clashed with during the campaign.

abstract: A U.S. tariff on laminated steel used in packaging will not apply to Tata Steel products manufactured in the Netherlands, the Dutch foreign trade minister said on Monday.
snippet: A U.S. tariff on laminated steel used in packaging will not apply to Tata Steel products manufactured in the Netherlands, the Dutch foreign trade minister said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: AMSTERDAM — A U.S. tariff on laminated steel used in packaging will not apply to Tata Steel products manufactured in the Netherlands, the Dutch foreign trade minister said on Monday.
headline_main: 100,000 Tons of Dutch-Made Tata Steel Exempt From U.S. Tariffs
headline_print_headline: 100,000 Tons of Dutch-Made Tata Steel Exempt From U.S. Tariffs

abstract: Senator Graham’s comment underscored how Bolton’s revelations may have increased the likelihood that the Senate will vote to hear from witnesses.
snippet: Senator Graham’s comment underscored how Bolton’s revelations may have increased the likelihood that the Senate will vote to hear from witnesses.
lead_paragraph: Republican defenders of President Trump on Monday redoubled their efforts to block any witnesses from being called in the impeachment trial in the wake of revelations from John R. Bolton, the president’s former national security adviser, that Mr. Trump directly linked Ukraine security aid to investigations of Democrats.

abstract: President Donald Trump hosted Israel’s prime minister and his chief rival Monday at the White House on the eve of unveiling a long-awaited Mideast peace plan, expressing confidence that despite adamant Palestinian rejection they would ultimately go along with a blueprint he said was “very good for them.”
snippet: President Donald Trump hosted Israel’s prime minister and his chief rival Monday at the White House on the eve of unveiling a long-awaited Mideast peace plan, expressing confidence that despite adamant Palestinian rejection they would ultimately g...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump hosted Israel’s prime minister and his chief rival Monday at the White House on the eve of unveiling a long-awaited Mideast peace plan, expressing confidence that despite adamant Palestinian rejection they would ultimately go along with a blueprint he said was “very good for them.”
headline_main: Trump Hosts Israeli Leaders Who Call His Peace Plan Historic
headline_print_headline: Trump Hosts Israeli Leaders Who Call His Peace Plan Historic

abstract: The judge overseeing Michael Avenatti's extortion trial said the case should not focus on Nike Inc's alleged corruption or devolve into celebrity name-dropping, as jury selection began for the case against the lawyer and critic of U.S. President Donald Trump.
snippet: The judge overseeing Michael Avenatti's extortion trial said the case should not focus on Nike Inc's alleged corruption or devolve into celebrity name-dropping, as jury selection began for the case against the lawyer and critic of U.S. President D...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The judge overseeing Michael Avenatti's extortion trial said the case should not focus on Nike Inc's alleged corruption or devolve into celebrity name-dropping, as jury selection began for the case against the lawyer and critic of U.S. President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Focus on Avenatti, U.S. Judge Says, as Trump Critic's Nike Extortion Trial Begins
headline_print_headline: Focus on Avenatti, U.S. Judge Says, as Trump Critic's Nike Extortion Trial Begins

abstract: Michael Avenatti, the celebrity lawyer and self-described high-profile nemesis of U.S. President Donald Trump, faces a trial on charges he tried to extort Nike Inc and defrauded a youth basketball coach he represented.
snippet: Michael Avenatti, the celebrity lawyer and self-described high-profile nemesis of U.S. President Donald Trump, faces a trial on charges he tried to extort Nike Inc and defrauded a youth basketball coach he represented.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Michael Avenatti, the celebrity lawyer and self-described high-profile nemesis of U.S. President Donald Trump, faces a trial on charges he tried to extort Nike Inc and defrauded a youth basketball coach he represented.
headline_main: Explainer: What to Expect at Michael Avenatti's Nike Extortion Trial in New York
headline_print_headline: Explainer: What to Expect at Michael Avenatti's Nike Extortion Trial in New York

abstract: The revelations by the former national security adviser, which the White House has had for weeks, angered some Republicans.
snippet: The revelations by the former national security adviser, which the White House has had for weeks, angered some Republicans.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s legal team’s second day of oral arguments in the Senate impeachment trial opens with fresh uncertainty on Monday, after The New York Times reported that the White House has for weeks had an unpublished manuscript by John R. Bolton, the former national security adviser, asserting that Mr. Trump refused to release military assistance for Ukraine until the country gave him investigative information about his political rivals.
headline_main: Republican senators privately complain they were blindsided by Bolton.

abstract: Bryant, 41, was traveling with his 13-year-old daughter to his youth basketball academy when they and seven other people perished in the crash. The helicopter had been given special approval to fly around Burbank in foggy weather.

abstract: President Trump also falsely claimed that Democrats had never asked Mr. Bolton to testify.
snippet: President Trump also falsely claimed that Democrats had never asked Mr. Bolton to testify.
lead_paragraph: “I NEVER told John Bolton that the aid to Ukraine was tied to investigations into Democrats, including the Bidens,” President Trump wrote just after midnight, referring to a widely debunked theory that the president had pursued about former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and his son Hunter.
headline_main: Trump denies Bolton’s account linking Ukraine’s aid to Biden investigations.

abstract: Until now, Mr. Trump seemed assured not only of acquittal but appeared likely to fend off the testimony of any more witnesses.
snippet: Until now, Mr. Trump seemed assured not only of acquittal but appeared likely to fend off the testimony of any more witnesses.
lead_paragraph: The news of John R. Bolton’s account describing how President Trump tied aid for Ukraine to investigations into the Bidens, given in an unpublished book, first reported by The New York Times, could hardly come at a worse time for Mr. Trump, just as his lawyers have opened his defense on the Senate floor.
